# Vocal-Scriber Environment Configuration
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env and replace the placeholder with your actual token
# 3. Never commit the .env file (it's already in .gitignore)

# HuggingFace API Token (Optional but Recommended)
# Enables faster model downloads from HuggingFace Hub
# Get your token at: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
# Permissions needed: Read access
HF_TOKEN=your_token_here

# Diarization Model Selection (Optional)
#
# IMPORTANT: Must be an MLX-format speech-to-text model
#
# Default: mlx-community/VibeVoice-ASR-bf16 (~9GB, best quality)
#
# Where to find compatible models:
#   1. Browse: https://huggingface.co/mlx-community
#   2. Search for: "VibeVoice" or "whisper mlx"
#   3. Look for models with "ASR" (Automatic Speech Recognition) in name
#   4. Model must be in MLX format (not PyTorch/ONNX)
#   5. Model must be compatible with mlx-audio library (mlx_audio.stt)
#
# Known compatible models:
#   - mlx-community/VibeVoice-ASR-bf16 (default, ~9GB, bfloat16, best quality)
#   - mlx-community/VibeVoice-ASR-int8 (~5GB, 8-bit quantized, balanced)
#   - mlx-community/VibeVoice-ASR-int4 (~3GB, 4-bit quantized, fastest/smallest)
#
# Note: Regular OpenAI Whisper models won't work - they must be converted
# to MLX format first. Look for models under mlx-community organization.
#
# Example usage:
# DIARIZE_MODEL=mlx-community/VibeVoice-ASR-int4
